v1.1.2 Phase 68 (2026.7.8, same-version revision):
  - Version remains versionCode=112, versionName="1.1.2".
  - Analyze All optimization (Issue 30): _reviewAnalyzeAdvance() (ui.js, GPL v3)
    now calls render() only every 10 steps (was: every step); intermediate
    steps use lightweight _refreshEvalTrendChart() + _updateReviewAnalyzeBtn().
    The next _requestBatchEval call is wrapped in setTimeout(0) to yield the
    main thread (prevents ANR on long games).
  - Long-press priority feature (Issue 30): move-list rows (.rmv-block) now
    have an oncontextmenu handler _prioritizeReviewStep (ui.js, GPL v3). Long-
    pressing an uncached move during an active batch sends engineStop(),
    pushes the step onto _reviewAnalyzePriorityQueue, fires Toast + haptic,
    and the next _reviewAnalyzeAdvance evaluates the prioritized step first.
    New state: _reviewAnalyzePriorityQueue (cleared on batch start/completion/
    cancel/exitReview/_resetGameUIState). New i18n keys (zh/en) in
    game-logic.js (AGPL v3): priority_eval_toast, priority_eval_already_cached,
    priority_eval_not_in_review.
  - CSS: .rmv-block (index.html.tpl, GPL v3) now has user-select:none +
    -webkit-touch-callout:none + touch-action:manipulation to prevent text
    selection during long-press.
  - Stats nav buttons (stats.html, GPL v3): changed from min-width:38px to
    flex:1 1 0 (uniform full-width, matches review-mode nav buttons).
  - PGN cache partial-eval dialog (ui.js, GPL v3): title now has emoji prefix;
    Android back-button dismisses via new _pgnPartialEvalDialogActive/
    _pgnPartialEvalDialogDismiss globals checked in handleBackPress().
  - License classification: unchanged — no new third-party code introduced.

v1.1.2 Phase 67 (2026.7.7):
  - Version bumped to versionCode=112, versionName="1.1.2".
  - Emoticon-text spacing fix: audited all i18n keys and hardcoded HTML
    titles; added a space between emoji and following text in 6 i18n keys
    (stats_title, stats_export_html, stats_review, save_pgn_prompt,
    variation_toggle, pgn_cache_manager — zh/en synchronized). Excluded
    VS15-decorated chess piece symbols (used as inline icons).
  - PGN cache [%eval] root-cause fix: _pgnCacheSaveCurrentImpl() now checks
    _reviewEvalCache coverage before rebuild; if incomplete AND in review
    mode AND not pure-import, shows a 3-option dialog (Analyze All first /
    Save anyway / Cancel). _reviewAnalyzeAdvance() completion path triggers
    deferred save via _pgnCacheSaveCurrentImpl_SkipCoverageCheck().
    _resetGameUIState() and exitReview() clear _pendingPGNCacheSave.
    5 new i18n keys (zh/en): pgn_cache_partial_eval_title/msg/
    analyze_first/save_as_is, pgn_cache_analyze_then_save. New dialog
    function _pgnCacheShowPartialEvalDialog().
  - Code-review fixes (P0/P1/P2/GOV/MED):
    * engine_jni.cpp nativeRenice() — added setpriority() return check +
      PRIO_MIN/PRIO_MAX range clamp + #include <errno.h> (GPL v3).
    * game-logic.js makeMv() — added inB() bounds check on to-coordinates
      (P1, GPL v3).
    * ai-bridge.js onHintMove() — added inB() bounds check on coords
      (P2, GPL v3); removed leftover console.log in onBestMove and
      onHintMove (Phase 66 cleanup miss).
    * StockfishNative.java Long.parseLong() — wrapped in try-catch
      (P2, GPL v3).
    * MainActivity.java onDestroy() WebView cleanup — added stopLoading()
      as step 0 (P3, AGPL v3).
    * ChessApp.java init log version v1.1.1 → v1.1.2 (AGPL v3).
    * ChessWebViewClient.java version comment v1.1.1 → v1.1.2 (AGPL v3).
    * StockfishNative.java ENGINE_VERSION v1.1.1 → v1.1.2 (GPL v3).
    * MainActivity.java VERSION v1.1.1 → v1.1.2 (AGPL v3).
    * strings.xml app_name "Regalia v1.1.1" → "Regalia v1.1.2" (AGPL v3).
    * game-logic.js loading_title v1.1.1 → v1.1.2 (GPL v3).
    * index.html.tpl <title> v1.1.1 → v1.1.2 (GPL v3).
    * ui.js header badge, about dialog, render-error page — version
      v1.1.1 → v1.1.2 (3 places, GPL v3).
    * build-chess.py — added __main__ guard + try/except around file I/O
      + missing-placeholder detection + explicit UTF-8 encoding (MED-3,
      AGPL v3).
    * gradle.properties — removed hardcoded Ubuntu JVM path
      org.gradle.java.home=/usr/lib/jvm/java-21-openjdk-amd64; JDK 21 now
      resolved via JAVA_HOME or ~/.gradle/gradle.properties (GOV-2, AGPL v3).
  - New files at project root: LICENSE (AGPL v3 full text — copy of
    LICENSE-AGPL v3, GOV-1, AGPL v3); version.properties (VERSION_MAJOR=1,
    VERSION_MINOR=1, VERSION_PATCH=2, VERSION_BUILD=112 — drives
    build.gradle's computedVersionCode/Name, AGPL v3); keystore.properties
    (release signing config — releaseKeystorePath/Password/KeyAlias/
    KeyPassword, AGPL v3, .gitignore'd in production).
  - License classification: unchanged — no new third-party code introduced.
    All Phase 67 changes are in GPL v3 files (engine_jni.cpp, game-logic.js,
    ai-bridge.js, pgn-standard.js, ui.js, index.html.tpl, chess.html,
    StockfishNative.java, StatsActivity.java — DroidFish-derived) or AGPL
    v3 files (chess960.js, eco-data.js, MainActivity.java, ChessApp.java,
    ChessWebViewClient.java, EngineService.java, StabilizationHelper.java,
    RootDetector.java, TlsSecurityHelper.java, CMakeLists.txt, build-chess.py,
    AndroidManifest.xml, strings.xml, res/xml/*.xml, build.gradle,
    settings.gradle, gradle.properties, version.properties,
    keystore.properties, LICENSE, UBIQUITOUS_LANGUAGE.md, NOTICE, README.md,
